title: Murdered Soul Suspect (j-TAG/RGH ONLY) XBOX360
description:
Murdered: Soul Suspect is an upcoming action-adventure video game, Co-developed by Square Enix Japan and Airtight Games and published by Square Enix. [3][4] The game will be released on Microsoft Windows, PlayStation 3, PlayStation 4, Xbox 360 and Xbox One. It has been targeted to release on June 3, 2014 in North America and on June 6, 2014 in Europe.[5]

The events of the game are set in Salem, Massachusetts, and focus on Detective Ronan O'Connor, who is slain by a brutal and relentless killer. Ronan returns as a ghost, and will not rest in peace until he solves his own murder by using his ghostly powers, and at the same time combat demonic creatures who wish to eat his soul. Along the way to finding his killer, Ronan is also helped by Joy, a girl who not only witnessed Ronan's death, but can also see and speak to ghosts (including Ronan), a trait she inherited from her missing mother, a contracted psychic.
